    <p>AF­TER­NOON TEA AT RAF­FLES HO­TEL</p>
    <p>By Fleur Vella-Chang Ethos Books/ Hard­cover/ $16.95/Avail­able at Ki­noku­niya</p>
    <p>“We got this book when Neil was a baby. I re­mem­ber how fas­ci­nated he was with the an­i­mals and land­marks. It even in­spired us to take him to the Sin­ga­pore Zoo for his first birth­day.”</p>
    <p>THE LIT­TLE SIN­GA­PORE BOOK</p>
    <p>By Sim Ee Waun and Joyce­line See Tully, il­lus­trated by Diane Ng Rose Pep­per Dog Press/Hard­cover/ $26.75/Avail­able at Ki­noku­niya</p>
    <p>LOST IN SIN­GA­PORE</p>
    <p>By Matthew Cooper, il­lus­trated by Candice Phang Kingfisher Books/ Paperback/ $14.98/ Avail­able at ma­jor book­stores</p>
    <p>“This is a lovely book about a boy and his ad­ven­ture in Sin­ga­pore, spark­ing the love for ex­plo­ration in the lit­tle ones. It even in­cludes el­e­ments of an­i­mal en­dan­ger­ment aware­ness which I re­ally like.”</p>
    <p>“This is packed with fan­tas­tic de­tails about Sin­ga­pore from the old Te­masek king­dom to present day.</p>
    <p>“The vi­brant il­lus­tra­tions add to the story, giv­ing a re­ally in-depth view on Sin­ga­pore’s his­tory for young read­ers.”</p>

